FeedPackage.Description: Created to avoid big libraries in my code. The aim is to keep things small and simple as long as possible. With this tiny library you can build object graphs and pull them out from the container at need. This was my primary requirement, and is what I'm already doing with several other containers. But the containers are pretty big and not everyone knows them well enough. Anyone can get to know these few hundered lines of code. For more information: http://steinardragsnes.blogspot.com/2012/02/kill-your-dependency-injection.html
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Version 1.0, used in production with a 95% test coverage.
FeedPackage.Summary: Tiny (500 lines) dependency injection library that will build your object graphs based on code configuration similar to Spring.Net's code configuration policy.
FeedPackage.Title: DependencyInjector

FeedPackage.Description: Tiny (500 lines) dependency injection library that will build your object graphs based on code configuration similar to Spring.Net's code configuration policy. Many traditional DI-containers are pretty big and solve too many problems. Containers may be easy to use, but they are complex and not everyone knows them well enough to bring that complexity into their projects. My aim is to keep things small and simple as long as possible and anyone can learn to know these few hundered lines of code. For more information: http://steinardragsnes.blogspot.com/2012/02/kill-your-dependency-injection.html

FeedPackage.Description:
DependencySharp allows you to embed unmanaged COM libraries within your managed library (as a byte array), and at runtime check if the unmanaged library exists in a specified location. If it doesn't, the library is automatically written to the specified location.
These "self-contained" libraries are capable of managing their own unmanaged dependencies, providing a convenient way for your end-user to use and deploy your managed library.
Full documentation and usage examples: https://github.com/evanwon/dependencysharp/blob/master/README.md
DependencySharp is open-source: https://github.com/evanwon/dependencysharp

FeedPackage.Description: DepMan is a dependency manager for cross-platform projects, like Xamarin, where some dependencies have do be injected.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: First release
FeedPackage.Summary: DepMan has a very simple interface; Get<T>() and Register<TInterface,TImplementor>(); You don't need to use the Register method if you decorate the implementing class with the [Implements(..)] attribute. DepMan creates only one instance of any class registered, which ensures that memory isn't wasted on multiple instances. The Get method performs a very fast lookup (O(1)) and returns the registered class (if any, otherwise throws exception). The 'Implements' attribute can be used to automatically register a class using the interface it implements as key.
FeedPackage.Tags: xamarin dependency manager service dependencies cross-platform DepMan
FeedPackage.Title: DepMan

FeedPackage.Description:
DequeNET (pronounced Deck Net) provides a concurrent lock-free deque C# implementation. A deque, or double-ended queue, is a data structure that allows insertion and removal of items on both ends. ConcurrentDeque<T> supports 6 operations in constant time O(1): PushRight, PopRight, PeekRight, PushLeft, PopLeft and PeekLeft.
The library also offers a simpler Deque<T> (not thread safe), implemented as a ring buffer. This implementation allows Pop and Peek operations to run in O(1) time and Push operations in amortized O(1) time.
